  "description": "A public-domain corpus of ancient Greek literature: 1,342 authors and 4,005 works spanning Homer through late antiquity. Includes philosophy, history, drama, lyric, medicine, mathematics, rhetoric, and the fragmentary traditions. Published in clean Unicode Greek as PDF, Markdown, plain text, and structured JSON, with English author metadata and biographies. Data store for the Eulogikon project.",
